The definition of `iIndepFun` for a function `f : α × ℕ → β` and a measure `μ` is that for any `n : ℕ`, the function `f n` is independent of `f k` for all `k < n`. In our case, `f` is `fun p ω => ω p.2 p.1`, which takes a pair `(p.1, p.2)` (where `p.1 : α` and `p.2 : ℕ`) and returns `ω p.2 p.1`.

